qas.question: What year did the CBC begin contributing funds to the show Doctor Who?
When did CBC end its Doctor Who contributions?

answers.text: the end of fourth season, broadcast in 2008

qas.question: Which Doctor Who spinoff did CBC contribute to?
Which Australian series has CBC taken interest in?

answers.text: Janet King and Love Child, and the comedy-drama series Please Like Me

qas.question: What was the CBC's most popular show in 2005?

context: Beginning in <a0_0>2005<a0_0/>, the CBC has contributed production funds for the BBC Wales revival of <b4_0>Doctor Who<b4_0/>, for which it received a special credit at the end of each episode. This arrangement continued until <a1_0>the end of fourth season, broadcast in <b6_0>2008<a1_0/>.<b6_0/> The CBC similarly contributed to the first season of the spin-off series, <a2_0><b5_0>Torchwood<a2_0/>.<b5_0/> More recently, the network has also begun picking up Canadian rights to some Australian series, including the drama series <a3_0><b7_0>Janet King and Love Child,<b7_0/> and the comedy-drama series Please Like Me<a3_0/>.
